---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/main.astro";
---

<MainLayout class="contentContainer">
  <article class="termsContent">
    <section class="header">
      <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
      <p class="lastUpdatedDate">Last updated: 17 July 2026</p>
    </section>

    <section class="termsBody">
      <p>This Cookie Policy explains how readthisshit.fyi ("RTS", "we", "our", or "us") uses cookies and similar technologies.</p>
      <p>
        For more information about how we process personal information, please read our
        <a href="/legal/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
      <p>Cookies are small text files stored on your device by your web browser.</p>
      <p>They help websites remember information such as your login session, preferences, and privacy choices.</p>
      <p>RTS only uses cookies that help provide and improve the Service.</p>

      <h2>2. Cookies We Use</h2>

      <h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
      <p>Essential cookies are required for RTS to function correctly.</p>
      <p>These cookies are used for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>signing you in;</li>
        <li>keeping you signed in;</li>
        <li>protecting your account;</li>
        <li>preventing abuse;</li>
        <li>remembering your cookie preferences;</li>
        <li>maintaining secure sessions.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You cannot disable essential cookies while using RTS because the Service depends on them.</p>

      <h3>Analytics Cookies</h3>
      <p>Analytics cookies help us understand how people use RTS.</p>
      <p>We use analytics to learn things such as:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>which pages are visited most often;</li>
        <li>how users navigate the website;</li>
        <li>which features are used;</li>
        <li>where users encounter problems;</li>
        <li>how we can improve usability and performance.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Analytics are never used to sell your personal information or display personalized advertising.</p>
      <p>Where required by law, analytics cookies are only used after you give your consent.</p>

      <h2>3. Analytics</h2>
      <p>RTS uses Umami Analytics.</p>
      <p>Umami helps us understand how the website is used through information such as:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>page views;</li>
        <li>button clicks;</li>
        <li>navigation paths;</li>
        <li>session recordings;</li>
        <li>heatmaps;</li>
        <li>feature usage;</li>
        <li>A/B testing;</li>
        <li>performance metrics.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This information helps us improve RTS and fix problems.</p>

      <h2>4. Managing Cookies</h2>
      <p>When you first visit RTS, you will be asked whether you want to allow analytics cookies.</p>
      <p>You can choose to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>accept analytics cookies;</li>
        <li>reject analytics cookies.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Essential cookies remain enabled because they are required for the Service to function.</p>
      <p>If cookie controls are available in your account settings, you can change your choice at any time.</p>
      <p>You can also delete or block cookies through your web browser. Doing so may prevent some parts of RTS from working correctly.</p>

      <h2>5. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
      <p>Some third-party services used by RTS may place cookies on your device.</p>
      <p>These services may include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Cloudflare;</li>
        <li>Better Auth;</li>
        <li>Umami Analytics.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Each provider is responsible for its own privacy practices.</p>
      <p>We recommend reviewing their privacy documentation if you would like more information.</p>

      <h2>6. Changes to This Cookie Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time.</p>
      <p>When we do, we will update the "Last updated" date at the top of this page.</p>
      <p>
        If a change significantly affects how cookies are used, we will make reasonable efforts to notify registered users before the change
        takes effect.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Contact</h2>
      <p>If you have questions about this Cookie Policy, please contact us.</p>
      <p>Email: <a href="mailto:mark@itsmark.dev">mark@itsmark.dev</a></p>
      <p>
        GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/readthisshit-fyi" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >https://github.com/readthisshit-fyi</a
        >
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</MainLayout>

<style lang="scss">
  .contentContainer {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .termsContent {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: var(--max-content-width);
    padding: 0 20px;

    .header {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: flex-start;
      height: auto;
      padding: 70px 0;

      h1 {
        color: var(--text);
        font-size: 48px;
        font-style: normal;
        font-weight: 600;
        line-height: normal;
        text-align: left;
        width: 100%;
        margin: 0 0 20px 0;
      }

      .lastUpdatedDate {
        text-align: left;
        width: 100%;
        font-size: 14px;
        color: var(--dimmed-text-two);
        padding: 0;
        margin: 0;
      }
    }

    .termsBody {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 20px;
      padding-bottom: 100px;

      p {
        color: var(--text);
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin: 0;

        a {
          color: var(--text);
          text-decoration: underline;
          transition: opacity 0.2s ease;

          &:hover {
            opacity: 0.7;
          }
        }
      }

      h2 {
        color: var(--text);
        font-size: 24px;
        font-style: normal;
        font-weight: 600;
        line-height: normal;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0 0 0 16px;
        border-left: 4px solid var(--text);
        opacity: 0.8;
      }

      h3 {
        color: var(--text);
        font-size: 20px;
        font-style: normal;
        font-weight: 600;
        line-height: normal;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0 0 0 12px;
        border-left: 2px solid var(--text);
        opacity: 0.8;
      }

      ul {
        list-style: none;
        padding-left: 20px;
        margin: 0;

        li {
          color: var(--text);
          font-size: 16px;
          line-height: 1.6;
          margin-bottom: 10px;
          position: relative;
          padding-left: 15px;

          &::before {
            content: "•";
            position: absolute;
            left: 0;
            font-weight: bold;
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .termsContent {
      .header {
        padding: 40px 0;

        h1 {
          font-size: 32px;
        }

        .lastUpdatedDate {
          font-size: 12px;
        }
      }

      .termsBody {
        gap: 16px;
        padding-bottom: 50px;

        p {
          font-size: 14px;
        }

        h2 {
          font-size: 20px;
        }

        h3 {
          font-size: 17px;
        }

        ul li {
          font-size: 14px;
        }
      }
    }
  }
</style>
